text.section:
A criminal garnishment applies to any of the following:
A convicted person's earnings as defined in KRS 427.005;
Indebtedness that is owed to a convicted person by a garnishee for amounts that are not earnings;
Money that is held by a garnishee on behalf of a convicted person;
The convicted person's personal property that is in the possession of a garnishee; or
If the garnishee is a corporation, shares or securities of a corporation or a proprietary interest in a corporation that belongs to a convicted person.
